## 20. Do Not Import Files Directly in Swift
In Swift (and Xcode), you must never import individual files by path (e.g., import MyProject.SomeFolder.MyFile).
You should only import entire modules (targets, frameworks, or packages), such as:
import SwiftUI
import Foundation
import MyCustomModule
If a protocol or type is defined in the same module/target, it is automatically visible—no import is needed.
If a protocol or type is defined in another module, use only the module name:
Apply to Waypoint.swi...
ModuleName
Never use a file path in an import statement!
Rationale:
Direct file imports are not supported in Swift and will cause build errors. This keeps your codebase modular, maintainable, and compatible with Swift best practices.

