App Architecture Principles:
Use Clean Architecture and MVVM.
Separate code into Presentation, Domain, Data (and optionally Application) layers.
Presentation: UI rendering, ViewModels, navigation, error handling, accessibility, performance.
Application: Orchestrates business processes, coordinates use cases, integrates with external systems.
Domain: Core business logic, use cases, entities, repository protocols, domain errors, domain events.
Data: Data sources, mapping, caching, error handling, synchronization.
Each layer only depends on the layer below it.
The Domain layer must not depend on UI or infrastructure.
All business rules and validation belong in the Domain layer.
Use repositories to abstract data sources.
Use dependency injection for testability.
Document complex business rules.
